ith dynamic testing, all the necessary documentation required by the regulatory authorities (EASA, FAA, Transport Canada, etc.) is provided for the certification of the products manufactured by AmSafe. Request Prototype TestingPrototype TestingFacilities Overview10,000 square feet of testing space2 operable sleds labs, including brand new 2.0 MN ServoSled with expanded instrumentationSleds include onboard high-speed cameras, lighting and expanded ATD inventory that meet the latest regulations for oblique and side facing seatsAircraft seat testing for structural integrity and occupant safety. We handle all test fixturing for most seatsIf your application requires specialized test requirements we can engineer, design and fabricate for all test designs10,000 sq.ft. of testing spaceProgram ManagementTrainingField SupportProgram ManagementAmSafe provides technical and program management support to meet customer requirements and expectations. Experienced Program Managers will develop complete project plans including scope and specifications for the design, development, testing, certification, production, installation design and integration for all AmSafe airbag systems.Customers of AmSafe airbag systems include airframe manufacturers, operators, and aircraft seat manufacturers. Extensive engineering experience and technical knowledge inspires confidence in AmSafe and AmSafe products. The Program Management and Technical Support teams have experience in all areas of aircraft certification and the regulatory approval process (Type Certification Modifications, Supplemental Type Certification programs).TrainingAmSafe provides training programs to meet customer’s specific training needs and objectives. Training can be coordinated onsite or via web-based formats. Training programs include general overview, product application, installation, maintenance and replacement of AmSafe Airbag system and components.AmSafe provides training courses to the customer audience including: Maintenance, Engineering, QA, Manufacturing, Shipping & Handling, or Flight Crew. AmSafe also delivers courses in train-the-trainer format which include interactive lectures, practical exercises and final evaluations. Request a trainingField SupportAmSafe Technical Support can support training, installations, technical analysis, repair and maintenance of AmSafe Airbag systems and components as required.AmSafe Program Managers are knowledgeable and experienced at identifying existing or potential issues, AmSafe Technical Support can help identify issues and address any concerns necessary to ensure all AmSafe airbag systems and components operate properly and safely in all environments. Request field supportRepair & OverhaulWith more than 40 years in the aviation restraint business, AmSafe has the knowledge and expertise to repair all your commercial and general aviation seatbelts and flight crew restraint systems.Repair and recondition nearly all restraints from every major airlineCertified to meet all aviation authority requirementsFull production testing using latest technology with expert engineering supportComplete with manufacturer’s warranty "AmSafe can inspect and repair your product to the highest regulatory standards." Find an AmSafe Authorized Service Center Select a regionNorth America - United StatesNorth America - MexicoNorth America - CanadaSouth America & CaribbeanAfricaEuropeAsia & Middle EastEastern Europe & RussiaAustralasia Select a country / state alabama alaska arizona arkansas california colorado connecticut delaware florida georgia hawaii idaho illinois indiana iowa kansas kentucky louisiana maine maryland massachusetts michigan minnesota mississippi missouri montana nebraska nevada new-hampshire new-jersey new-mexico new-york north-carolina north-dakota ohio oklahoma oregon pennsylvania south-carolina south-dakota tennessee texas utah vermont virginia washington wisconsin wyoming Select a country / state mexico Select a country / state canada Sel