AmSafe, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 1:03 AM ET
Aerospace and Defense

Company Overview of AmSafe, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
AmSafe, Inc. designs, manufactures, and supports engineered textile and safety restraint products for aerospace, defense, civil aviation, and specialty vehicle industries in the United States and internationally. The company offers airbags and restraints, interior products, and maintenance/repair/overhaul services for commercial aviation; aircraft retrofit with seatbelt airbags, seatbelt airbags, traditional restraints, business jet restraints, and rotorcraft restraints, as well as operates as a service center for seatbelt airbags; and ground restraint systems for defense. Its clients include customers and respective authorities, such as Federal Aviation Administration, European Aviation Saf...
AmSafe, Inc. designs, manufactures, and supports engineered textile and safety restraint products for aerospace, defense, civil aviation, and specialty vehicle industries in the United States and internationally. The company offers airbags and restraints, interior products, and maintenance/repair/overhaul services for commercial aviation; aircraft retrofit with seatbelt airbags, seatbelt airbags, traditional restraints, business jet restraints, and rotorcraft restraints, as well as operates as a service center for seatbelt airbags; and ground restraint systems for defense. Its clients include customers and respective authorities, such as Federal Aviation Administration, European Aviation Safety Agency, Ministry of Defense, Department of Defense, and Department of Transportation. The company was founded in 1985 and is based in Phoenix, Arizona with manufacturing operations and service facilities in the United States, the United Kingdom, China, Sri Lanka, and internationally. As of February 15, 2012, AmSafe, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of TransDigm Inc.
Detailed Description


